59. $f = \\frac{2x}{x+3}, g = \\frac{5}{x}$.  Domain of f is all but x = -3, 
so g has to be restricted to not contain g = -3, which happens when $x = -5/3$.  So the domain of the composition is $x\neq -5/3, x\neq 0$.  The composition $\f\circ g = \\frac{10/x}{5/x + 3}=\\frac{10}{5+3x}$ which has domain $x\neq -5/3$.

61. same

